originalText.text: It's a shame how some officer can't be polite to small children especially when standing in front of the daycare! I have taught my son to be respectful and to always greet the officers when he encountered them. My 3yr old kept saying hi and they completely ignore him. As a parent, see 2 officers and yellow tapes around the school you will always think the worst. That something happened. Then I asked them if everything was alright and there were very dismissive and after several times of me asking they finally told that they just surveilling the area, but 2 officers spend most of their mornings on their cellphones! Great Job!

originalText.text: Hats off to the 33 !  I used to drive through this neighborhood back in the early 90's and it there was so much crime and it was very drug infested and run down neighborhood.What a complete overhaul the 33 has done in the neighborhood ,I didn't even recognize 178th and Amsterdam .Looks cleaned up.  Thank You to the men & women in Blue at the 33 !

originalText.text: I keep calling them about the noise from Third Palm Tree Bar and nothing happens. I do the whole 311 complaints and nothing. It was ridiculous tonight and the patrons of that bar made so much noise like animals inside and outside the bar. Yelling at the top of their lungs. The music got louder and louder. Someone on the mic amping up the people more. The bass sounds like a jack hammer and feels like one. The 33rd precinct has not done anything to help. Years long situation. There has been fights and shooting in the bar and police don't step in. This is the neverending story.
